cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is about using machine learning and deep learning approaches to capture sentence semantics in biomedical and clinical domains. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of pre-trained sentence embeddings, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (finding similar sentences in electronic medical records), which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of deep learning approaches also suggests the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with electronic medical records, which involves issues related to cybersecurity and privacy, suggesting the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
